# Terminal and tool permissions — non-destructive allowlist

This project permits the following **non-destructive** commands and tools. The AI may use or suggest these without treating them as requiring extra approval.

## Allowed commands and tools

- **Tools:** WebSearch, WebFetch (MCP or built-in)
- **Shell / env:** source, export
- **HTTP / data:** curl, jq
- **File read / inspect:** cat, ls, head, tail, file, wc, grep
- **Navigation / info:** pwd, which
- **File create (non-destructive):** mkdir, touch
- **Search / diff:** find, sort, tree, diff
- **Runtime / package manager:** node, npm, npx
- **Git (read-only):** git status, git diff, git log

## Out of scope (require explicit approval or are disallowed)

- Destructive or overwriting: rm, git push, git reset --hard, force flags
- Publish / deploy: npm publish, production deploys
- Secrets / env: never log or echo secrets; never commit .env

## Applying this in Cursor

To have these run automatically without a prompt, add the same commands to **Settings > Cursor Settings > Agents > Auto-Run > Command Allowlist** (or choose "Add to allowlist" when a sandboxed command fails). This file is the project’s source of truth for what is considered safe and allowed.
